# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Nightjar .gitignore — local-first AI assistant (AGPL-3.0-or-later)
# Goal: keep source + docs + config + license/attribution; exclude secrets,
# machine/user data, huge model weights, and re-generatable/vendored trees.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Secrets / credentials / accounts (defensive — NONE are committed today) ──
# Real email/CalDAV creds are Fernet-encrypted into ~/.nightjar/odysseus (OUTSIDE
# this repo); these patterns make sure a stray copy never lands in git.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.env
.envrc
accounts.json
secrets.json
credentials.json
*.credentials
*secret*.json
# Odysseus key material (normally ~/.nightjar/odysseus/.app_key & .key)
.app_key
.key
# Keys / certs
*.pem
*.p12
*.pfx
*.der
id_rsa*
id_ed25519*
*_rsa
*.keystore

# ── Nightjar runtime data dir (in case DATA_DIR is ever pointed into the repo) ─
.nightjar/
**/.nightjar/

# ── Model weights / large binaries (live in ~/.nightjar/models & ~/models) ────
*.gguf
*.ggml
*.onnx
*.safetensors
*.pt
*.pth
*.bin
voices-*.bin
Modelfile.*
# Ollama blobs (normally ~/.ollama — ignore defensively if ever copied in)
.ollama/

# ── Python ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
venv/
.venv/
env/
**/venv/
**/.venv/
__pycache__/
**/__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# ── Node / JS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
node_modules/
**/node_modules/
.npm/
.pnpm-store/
# (package-lock.json / pnpm-lock.yaml are KEPT — reproducible installs)

# ── Build / bundler output (re-generatable) ──────────────────────────────────
dist/
build/
out/
**/out/
.vite/
**/.vite/
*.tsbuildinfo

# ── Logs / temp ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.log
logs/
tts_out.wav
*.tmp
.cache/

# ── Vendored / cloned UPSTREAM reference repos (each is its own huge git repo) ─
# NOTE (read before committing): research/ holds full clones of OpenCode,
# Row-Bot, Odysseus, Open WebUI, orb-ui, gemma-chat (~3 GB, each with its own
# .git). They are ignored here because they are re-clonable upstream references
# and bloat/complicate this repo. TWO consequences to handle deliberately:
#   1. research/odysseus is a RUNTIME dependency (the Odysseus MCP sidecar runs
#      python from research/odysseus/...). A fresh clone of Nightjar will NOT run
#      the Odysseus tier without it — provide it via a submodule or a setup step.
#   2. The Odysseus AGPL attribution (research/odysseus/{LICENSE,ACKNOWLEDGMENTS.md,
#      licenses/}) is required to ship — since research/ is ignored, ensure those
#      files ship another way (submodule, or copy into a committed location).
#   (Row-Bot attribution is already self-contained: vendored under
#    phase2-mcp/nightjar_capabilities/_vendor/ + phase2-mcp/NOTICE + LICENSE.row-bot.)
research/

# ── OS / editor cruft ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.idea/
# VS Code: keep shared settings if you add them; ignore per-machine noise
.vscode/*
!.vscode/extensions.json
!.vscode/settings.json

# ── Local tooling state ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock
.openforge/
